content:
Data preparation is a process of iterative refinement. As you dig deeper into your data, new clues emerge. Discoveries can cause you to reassess previous assumptions and adjust your data prep implementation accordingly.

Einstein Discovery requires a CRM Analytics dataset with at least 3 columns: one outcome variable plus two explanatory or predictor variables. It supports datasets with up to 50 variables but solutions typically succeed with far fewer. To build models, Einstein Discovery requires a CRM Analytics dataset that has at least 400 observations with a known outcome.

Consider Prior Record States

If you want to capture changes in data over a time period, determine whether your data source keeps only the current state values of a record. If not, consider storing a snapshot of the historical data or keeping prior value data in custom fields.

Determine the Appropriate Level of Granularity for the Insights You Want

What level of insights are of interest to achieve the objective? For example, customer-level insights are of interest when looking at customer revenue. Use grouping to adjust the granularity of the data and choose a granularity that is actionable, understandable, and useful.

A common mistake is to overly aggregate data. Keep the desired outcome in mind and use data collected in rows at that level of granularity. Data analyzed in Excel can be at a different level from what you want for Einstein Discovery.

Determine Relevant Time Frames

Statistical analysis datasets can summarize a lifetime of values in just one single row, with many columns that describe different points in time. Don't collect a lifetime of fields if a specific window of time more accurately reflects the outcome variable you want to analyze and predict.

To use Einstein Discovery for predictions, your variables must be at the point in time on which the prediction is based.

Decide How Much Data to Get

To build reliable predictive models, provide Einstein Discovery with enough data that reflects what actually happens in the real world. Consider collecting data from different time periods if time sequences are important in predictions.

Consider Bias and Fairness in Your Data

Does the data you want to use reflect business practices that are possibly biased or unfair? To help you produce ethical and accountable insights and models, Einstein Discovery detects proxy variables and disparate impacts in your dataset.

Analyze Without Overfitting or Underfitting

Einstein Discovery figures out which variables and combinations of variables best explain the behavior of your chosen metric without overfitting or underfitting.
title: Data Preparation Requirements for Einstein Discovery
